cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.DS

This paper presents a modified Cross-Entropy Method (CEM) that uses a masked auto-regressive neural network for modeling uniform distributions over the solution space. The paper also uses maximum entropy policy gradient methods from Reinforcement Learning to train the model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with optimization and constraint satisfaction, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
